The memorial service for Philippus Andrias (Flip) Benade, owner of South Gate Lodge will be held at Rakgolo Hall, South-Gate along the R37 to Lebowakgomo this morning (Monday) at 11:00. Benade, described as the heart and soul of South-Gate passed away Thursday at the age of 78. The family invites those interested to join the family in celebrating his life as loving husband, father, grandfather, mentor and friend. Story: RC Myburgh &gt;&gt;rc.observer@gmail.com Featured photo: Flip Benade, founder and owner of South-Gate Lodge passed away at the age of 78.